# Translation Alignment

When updating user-facing copy in `messages/*.json`:

- If a key's text changes in one locale, update the same key in all supported locales in the same task.
- If a new key is added in one locale, add it in all locale files before finishing.
- If a key is removed or renamed, apply the same removal/rename across all locale files.
- Do not leave mixed messaging for the same key across locales unless the user explicitly requests locale-specific wording.

## Required check before finishing

- Verify the edited key set is identical across all `messages/*.json` files.
- Verify changed keys have updated values in each locale (not just English).

## Example

- Changed `Tool.supportPromptInFlow` in `messages/en.json`?
  - Also update `Tool.supportPromptInFlow` in `messages/fr.json`, `messages/de.json`, `messages/es.json`, `messages/pt.json`, `messages/ja.json`, `messages/ar.json`, and `messages/zh.json`.
